About me!

Graduation 2028 School Pocomoke High School My aspire towards Comp Sci Knowledge is to become very smart and create apps for people work or even make my own company directing to Comp Sci. And I love learning new things! This Web page will be about my expierence and everything I have done in computer science classes. At the moment I am taking 2 classes such as CSE and Foundations of computer science.

In these classes I have made multiple apps and coding languages. For example the first langauage we started with was Block Coding. These are the apps and projects we have created.

Classes I will be taking are CSE, CSP, CSA, Cyber Security. (I will link my pages for those classes in the future when completed.) Some things I have done already in CSE are multiple projects, for example I created a game that can cure boredom. Here are the images to the game. Vladimir Bowling:

User Story: I created this app using my creativity. I had a hard time thinking about what to make but than I thought of an idea. I looked at 2 games we made in the past and I combined them and even added my own features to it. So i started the mix by adding the image sprite increase in speed and the timers to count down as I play and when my score goes up the longer I am alive in the game. The past games that I am referring to is ("Happy Face Game" , "Guessing Game"). The way these two games relate to mines is by the timer and the moving image sprite.

Hydrations: Image Sprite Moving , Procedures , Event handlers. With these hydrations and blocks it helped be be able to create the type of processes like being able to make sounds play during the game and also make an image show up during a certain stage of the app. I also added working timer and score board that functions correctly. I added a win or lose label at the top to make sure my players know if they won or lost.

Backlog Items: I ran across some problems during this project but i was able to make improvements and fix them, for example he problem I had was that the image would not show because I had codes created that didn't cooperate with the others. I went around asking others to try and play and look through so I can find a solution and make the game better for others so they can be satisfied. The problems that occured were the images not showing up and my timer going still even after the game ended.( The way I fixed this was by asking my class mates for some input and maybe something that could help me).  So I made it to where, IF game ended THEN happy face visible is FALSE and sad face visible TRUE. Than I would make a global variable for the timer and set it to 300 seconds. So i made a code where i set the global timer to decrease by one every time till the game has ended with a clock event handler.

Reflection: I used many eventhandlers and more blocks in this program such as procedures, variables, math blocks, eventhanders and others. Some new things i added on my game was the speed concept. The longer I last the faster the image gets. I also added a Timer (Clock) and a score board to make sure that the players know the score they got and how much time they have left or how long they were alive for.
